Your `buttonHandlerOf` is incorrect. You can&#39;t render a view from it. Generally you&#39;d need to set the response data to state, which would be then rendered. 

Also I&#39;d recommend you to make those view functions that return JSX into separate React components.

```
 const buttonHandlerOf = alpha2Code =&gt; {
    const url = `https://restcountries.eu/rest/v2/alpha/${alpha2Code}`;

    return axios.get(url).then(response =&gt; {
      console.log(response.data);
      console.log(response.data.languages);
      setCountries([response.data]) // set the country to the state here
    });
  };
```

As pointed in the comments, this would remove all other countries, so you could fetch them again when the filter is cleared:
```
 useEffect(() =&gt; {
    if (!filter) {
      axios
        .get(&quot;https://restcountries.eu/rest/v2/all&quot;)
        .then(response =&gt; setCountries(response.data));
    }
  }, [filter]);
```
Alternatively you could add a reset button.

